---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const site = Astro.site ?? new URL('https://www.usdtoworld.com');
const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: site.toString() },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'About Us', item: new URL('/about', site).toString() },
  ],
};
---
<Layout
  title="About Us | UsdtoWorld Currency Converter"
  description="Learn about UsdtoWorld, a free live currency converter for USD to RMB and 180+ other currency pairs."
  path="/about"
  schema={[breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <div class="container page-hero">
    <Breadcrumbs trail={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'About Us', href: '/about' }]} />
  </div>
  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container prose">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>About UsdtoWorld</h1>
      <p>
        UsdtoWorld started as a simple idea: currency conversion tools online are often cluttered with ads,
        slow to load, or buried behind sign-up walls. We built a fast, free, and accurate converter focused on
        the pair people search for most — USD to RMB — while supporting 180+ other currencies for everyday use.
      </p>

      <h2>What we do</h2>
      <p>
        UsdtoWorld pulls live exchange-rate data and presents it in a clean, mobile-first interface. Every
        conversion runs instantly in your browser, your recent lookups are saved locally on your device, and
        the site works even when you briefly lose connection by falling back to the last saved rate.
      </p>

      <h2>Our tools</h2>
      <p>
        Everything on UsdtoWorld is built around one goal: getting you a trustworthy number in as few taps as
        possible. Rather than bundling a single generic calculator, we've broken the experience into a handful
        of small, focused tools that each solve a specific part of the currency-conversion problem — whether
        you're checking today's USD to RMB rate, planning a transfer, or just curious how the yuan has moved
        over the past year.
      </p>

      <h3>Live currency converter</h3>
      <p>
        The core tool is the converter itself, front and center on the homepage. Type an amount, choose a
        "from" and "to" currency from more than a dozen supported options — including USD, RMB/CNY, PKR, MXN,
        INR, EUR, GBP, JPY, and more — and the result updates instantly using a live market data feed. We've
        also added one-tap shortcuts for the conversions people ask for most: 1 USD to RMB, 100 USD to RMB,
        1000 USD to RMB, and quick-access buttons for popular pairs like INR to USD and USD to PKR, so you
        don't have to re-type an amount every time you want to check a common figure.
      </p>

      <h3>Historical rate trends</h3>
      <p>
        A single number rarely tells the whole story. That's why we pair the live converter with a simplified
        12-month trend view, so you can see at a glance whether a pair like USD to RMB has been drifting up,
        drifting down, or holding roughly steady before you rely on today's figure for a bigger decision. It's
        intentionally lightweight — a quick visual gut-check, not a full charting platform — with a link back
        to the live converter for the precise, current rate.
      </p>

      <h3>Multi-language, multi-currency support</h3>
      <p>
        Currency conversion is a global need, so the interface itself isn't locked to English. You can switch
        the converter, navigation, and result labels into Hindi, Chinese, Spanish, or Japanese from the
        language selector in the header, with your choice remembered on your next visit. On the currency side,
        we go well beyond the headline USD/RMB pair, supporting dozens of currencies so the same tool that
        handles "1000 USD to RMB" can just as easily handle a Mexican peso, Philippine peso, or Hong Kong
        dollar conversion without switching sites.
      </p>

      <h3>Built to work offline and remember your history</h3>
      <p>
        UsdtoWorld is set up as a lightweight installable web app. The last successfully fetched exchange
        rates are cached on your device, so if you lose signal mid-trip or your connection briefly drops, the
        converter keeps working with the most recent numbers it has, and clearly flags that you're viewing a
        cached rate rather than a live one. Alongside that, a small "recently viewed" panel keeps track of the
        pairs and amounts you've checked most recently, so a repeat lookup — like your usual USD to RMB
        transfer amount — is one tap away instead of a fresh search.
      </p>

      <h3>Copy, share, and quick actions</h3>
      <p>
        Once you have a result, getting it out of the browser and into a message, spreadsheet, or email should
        be effortless. Every conversion includes a one-tap copy button that grabs a clean, formatted summary
        of the amount and rate, plus a share option on devices that support it, so you can send a conversion
        straight to a friend, client, or colleague without manually retyping numbers.
      </p>

      <h3>A growing answer bank</h3>
      <p>
        Beyond the calculator itself, we maintain a set of straightforward answers to the questions people
        actually search for around USD, RMB, and other major pairs — things like why the yuan moves the way
        it does, how it compares to currencies like the Indian rupee, and what factors tend to push exchange
        rates up or down. The goal is the same as with the tools: give you a fast, honest, well-sourced answer
        rather than a wall of jargon, and point you toward professional advice when a decision genuinely
        depends on it. We keep adding to this over time as new questions and new currency pairs come up, so
        it's worth checking back if the pair or topic you're after isn't covered yet.
      </p>

      <h2>Our approach</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No account required, no paywalls, no dark patterns.</li>
        <li>Rates sourced from a live market data feed, refreshed regularly.</li>
        <li>Built with performance and accessibility as first-class requirements, not afterthoughts.</li>
        <li>Available in English, Hindi, Chinese, Spanish, and Japanese.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>A note on accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        We aim for accuracy, but exchange rates shift constantly and every provider — including banks and card
        networks — applies its own margin. Please read our <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a> before making
        financial decisions based on figures shown here.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Questions, feedback, or a currency pair you'd like added? Visit our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
